graphy information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435795/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-07","Child Tax Credits: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people received child tax credits in (a) Houghton and Sunderland South constituency and (b) the North East in each year for which figures are available; and what the mean, mode, median and range is of tax credit payments made in those areas in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","19012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435796","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-10","<p>The latest information on the number of tax credit recipients in the Dundee City local authority can be found in table 3 of the April 2015 Personal Tax Credits provisional awards geographical analyses published statistics, found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-provisional-awards-geographical-analyses-december-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-provisional-awards-geographical-analyses-december-2013</a></p><p>These statistics are published in April and December each year.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-12-10T16:08:31.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435796/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435796/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-07","Welfare Tax Credits: Dundee","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how  many (a) households and (b) people are in receipt of tax credits in Dundee; and how many children are in each such household.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","19046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435797","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-10","<p>No estimate has been made of the change in income tax receipts arising from net migration.</p><br /><p>Since May 2010 the Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) has served as the Government’s independent fiscal watchdog. This includes responsibility for issuing five-year forecasts for the economy and public finances, at least twice a year, and assessment of the key sensitivities to this medium term forecast.</p><br /><p>The OBR has not viewed changes to net migration as one of the key risks or sensitivities to the medium term forecast.</p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-12-10T16:41:24.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435797/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435797/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-07","Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the change in tax income receipts arising from net migration being limited to tens of thousands.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","19047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435798","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The information requested can only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:24:41.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435798/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435798/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) social and (b) affordable housing tenants in receipt of housing benefit who have paid rents in excess of local housing allowance rates in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435799","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-22","<p>In 2013-14, there were around 91,000 single people under the age of 35 with no dependent children on at least one social housing waiting list in England. This is down from 124,000 in 2004-5 and 110,000 in 2010-11. (Source: English Housing Survey, Department for Communities and Local Government).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-12-22T12:37:58.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435799/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435799/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-07","Social Rented Housing: Waiting Lists","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many single people under the age of 35 with no dependent children are registered on waiting lists for social housing.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435800","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The introduction of Local Housing Allowance limits to housing benefit and Universal Credit houisng element awards will only apply from April 2018, where new tenancies have been taken out or renewed after April 2016.</p><br /><p>Tenants who take on a new tenancy or renew a tenancy will have the opportunity to consider whether they can afford to take on the property before committing to it. Because of the element of choice it is not possible to accurately estimate whether there will be any impact upon homelessness or the availability of social housing.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:58:16.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435800/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435800/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of restricting housing benefit entitlement for single social tenants under the age of 35 to the Shared Accommodation Rate of the relevant Local Housing Allowance on (a) levels of homelessness and (b) the availability of social housing for that age group.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435801","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>Capping high social sector rents at the relevant Local Housing Allowance rate does not come into effect until April 2018 and then only where a new tenancy is taken out or a tenancy is renewed after April 2016 and the resulting social rent charged exceeds the appropriate Local Housing Allowance rate for the size of household in the area at that time</p><br /><p>Because a range of factors will influence where and when a cap is applied, including behavioural responses from both claimants and landlords, it is not possible to assess the potential effect of the policy on social housing supply.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:51:07.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435801/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435801/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of capping housing benefit for social tenants at the relevant Local Housing Allowance rate on social housing supply.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435802","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>Capping high social sector rents at the relevant Local Housing Allowance rate does not come into effect until April 2018 and then only where a new tenancy is taken out or a tenancy is renewed after April 2016 and the resulting social rent charged exceeds the appropriate Local Housing Allowance rate for the size of household in the area at that time.</p><p>Because a range of factors will influence where and when a cap is applied, including behavioural responses from both claimants and landlords, it is not possible to assess the potential effect of the policy on the incomes of the tenants affected.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:35:14.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435802/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435802/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the effect of capping housing benefit for social tenant at the relevant Local Housing Allowance rate on the incomes of the tenants affected.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435803","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-15","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-12-15T15:41:01.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435803/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435803/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-07","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many single people under the age of 35 with no dependent children were accepted by local authorities as (a) homeless and (b) homeless and in priority need in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435804","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-15","<p>The Spending Review and Autumn Statement announced that funding of the Temporary Accommodation management fee will be devolved to local authorities from 2017/18, giving them more freedom and flexibility in how they use this funding. Current levels of funding will be maintained and, in addition, councils will receive £10 million a year more. The Department for Communities and Local Government will set out the precise detail of how the new funding will be distributed in 2016/17. The Department will work closely with local authorities and other partners to ensure that funding will be allocated in order to most effectively help councils tackle homelessness.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","18895 ; 19078","2015-12-15T15:42:31.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435804/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435804/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-07","Temporary Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to paragraph 1.149 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, how local authority funding allocations for temporary accommodation will be calculated over the Spending Review period.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435805","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-15","<p>The Spending Review and Autumn Statement announced that funding of the Temporary Accommodation management fee will be devolved to local authorities from 2017/18, giving them more freedom and flexibility in how they use this funding. Current levels of funding will be maintained and, in addition, councils will receive £10 million a year more. The Department for Communities and Local Government will set out the precise detail of how the new funding will be distributed in 2016/17. The Department will work closely with local authorities and other partners to ensure that funding will be allocated in order to most effectively help councils tackle homelessness.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","18896 ; 19078","2015-12-15T15:42:31.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435805/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435805/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-07","Temporary Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to paragraph 1.149 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, what steps his Department plans to take to assist local authorities for which the cost of providing temporary accommodation exceeds their pre-allocated share of funding.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435806","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The introduction of Local Housing Allowance limits to social sector tenants in receipt of Housing Benefit or the Universal Credit houisng element will only apply from April 2018, where new tenancies have been taken out or renewed after April 2016.</p><br /><p>Tenants who take on a new tenancy or renew a tenancy will have the opportunity to consider whether they can afford to take on the property before committing to it. Because of the element of choice is it not possible to accurately estimate the number of (a) social and (b) affordable housing tenants who will be affected by this measure.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:32:55.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435806/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435806/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435806/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) social and (b) affordable housing tenants who will be affected by planned caps on housing benefit in the social sector in (i) 2018-19, (ii) 2019-20 and (iii) 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435807","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The information requested can only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><br /> <br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:21:23.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435807/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435807/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435807/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) local authorities and (b) housing associations that have charged rents in excess of local housing allowance rates in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435808","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The information requested can only be provided at a disproportion cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:29:20.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435808/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435808/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435808/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Local Housing Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of homes for (a) social and (b) affordable rent which are let at rents at or below the shared accommodation rate of the local housing allowance in each region in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435809","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-14","<p>The Chancellor announced in the Spending Review 2015 that government will invest £150 million to support the British Museum, Science Museum and Victoria and Albert Museum to replace out of date museum storage at Blythe House with new world-class storage facilities with public access. The allocations to each museum are yet to be determined.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-14T16:00:12.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435809/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435809/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435809/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Museums and Galleries: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to paragraph 1.273 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, how much funding he plans to provide to the (a) Science Museum, (b) Victoria and Albert Museum and (c) British Museum.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","18882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435810","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-15","<p>The initiative will be administered by local authorities who will provide a code to eligible homes and businesses upon request. The code does not have a specific fixed value, but when used to obtain a satellite broadband service from one of the selected retail service providers, the use of the code will reduce the total cost (i.e. installation and commissioning costs plus 12 monthly subscriptions) by around £350.</p><br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-15T10:58:01.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435810/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435810/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to his Department's rural satellite broadband voucher scheme, what estimate he has made of the average cost of (a) installation and (b) a 12 months subscription to 2 megabit rural satellite broadband services.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435811","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-15","<p>The budget is £60 million,funded from the Local Body contracts with BT.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-15T10:35:02.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435811/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435811/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the planned budget is for the rural satellite broadband voucher scheme; and from which of his Department's funding headings that budget has been allocated.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435812","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-14","<p>Officials have held discussions with the European Commission on the compatibility of a new Horserace Betting Right with the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-14T14:26:39.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435812/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435812/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435812/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Horse Racing: Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to paragraph 2.152 of Budget 2015, published in March 2015, whether his Department has had discussions with the European Commission on the compatibility of the Horserace Betting Right with the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435813","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-15","<p>Four suppliers are currently providing access to satellite broadband through the government’s subsidy scheme: Avonline, Corsat, Digiweb, and Primetech. Further suppliers are in the process of seeking to join the scheme.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-15T10:10:34.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435813/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435813/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which suppliers will accept rural satellite broadband vouchers.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435814","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-14","<p>To inform work to replace the current levy system, we have commissioned an independent economic analysis of the costs and funding of horseracing. This economic analysis work will also examine relevant comparable models</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-14T14:39:09.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435814/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435814/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435814/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Horse Racing: Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department has examined the funding of horseracing from remote gambling in France and Ireland to inform its policy on the funding of horseracing in Britain.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435815","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-09","<p>The contract relating to West Ham United Football Club's use of the Olympic Stadium is between the West Ham and the London Legacy Development Corporation (LLDC). Any decision regarding whether to release contract details is a matter for the LLDC.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-09T11:52:34.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435815/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435815/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435815/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","West Ham United Football Club: Sportsgrounds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether he has had discussions with the (a) London Legacy Development Corporation (LLDC) and (b) Mayor of London on releasing the LLDC West Ham United Football Club contract.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","18941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435816","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","<p>Yes. Extensive and reliable mobile connectivity is vital for our modern economy, particularly in rural areas. The Government has undertaken a review of the planning system to assess what improvements should be made to support the deployment of mobile infrastructure. The outcome of that review will be announced shortly, I hope.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T12:53:56.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435816/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435816/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435816/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Mobile Phones: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 20 July 2015 to Question 6371, whether he plans to reform the planning process to improve the ability of mobile network operators to deploy taller infrastructure in areas where connectivity is needed; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","18847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435817","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","DCMS is investing £1.5 million in the Ferens Gallery to help them host the Turner Prize; plus £0.5 million to help create a lasting cultural legacy for Hull. The Gallery will receive a further £0.5m from ACE for refurbishment. My department is also providing £3.1 million to three ACE-funded organisations -Artlink, Freedom Festival and Hull Truck Theatre - who will play a key role in the 2017 events. Hull Museums, now among ACE's Major Partner Museums, have been awarded £2.5m between now and 2018; and an additional £3 million from ACE will help raise the profile of culture in the city and promote new partnerships throughout 2017. This amounts to over £11 million and does not include additional investment that might come from other bodies such as the BBC. <br />","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T12:19:44.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435817/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435817/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435817/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","UK City of Culture: Kingston Upon Hull","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much (a) capital funding and (b) funding in total has been allocated by (i) his Department and (ii) bodies funded by his Department to support Hull City of Culture 2017.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","18931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435818","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","<p>BT have madea public commitment to answer at least 80% of calls in the UK by the end of 2016. They also have planstoinvestin new tools for call centres and customers over the next 18 months to make it easier to get help; ensurethat customers with complex issues have a UK-based case handler; work to simplify bills and charges; and to increase the UK capacity in its call centres in the evenings and at weekends. I shall be watching their progress with interest, as I am sure will be my Rt Hon friend.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T12:47:48.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435818/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435818/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435818/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","British Telecom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the outcomes were of his recent meetings with BT's Head of Customer Care in relation to (a) billing, (b) transparency around charges, (c) customer care and (d) other issues that were discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Dr Liam Fox","North Somerset","Dr Liam Fox","18998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435819","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","The Museum of Design, V&amp;A Dundee will be a key central feature of the Dundee Waterfront Regeneration project. The Heritage Lottery Fund has contributed almost £14 million to the museum. The project is yet another example among many of a major national museum supporting culture outside London.","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T12:21:26.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435819/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435819/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435819/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-07","Regeneration: Dundee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what financial support the Government has provided for the Waterfront regeneration project in Dundee.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","19033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435820","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-15","<p>Work will commence on the next <em>UK Air and Space Doctrine</em> in the summer of 2016 and it is expected to be published in 2017. As with the previous version published in 2013, the RAF will consult widely across Defence as well as in the academic community. Research will draw on similar work from sources such as NATO and the United States Air Force.</p><p>In addition, the Development Concepts and Doctrine Centre (DCDC) will review the related Joint Doctrine Note (JDN): The UK Approach to Unmanned Systems. The intention is to publish the revised doctrine by autumn 2016.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-15T16:18:19.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435820/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435820/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435820/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-07","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, who his Department has consulted on the development of the UK's Air Power Doctrine; and when he expects to publish that doctrine.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","19035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435821","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-15","<p>Work on the last refit of HMS Ocean began in December 2012 and was completed in August 2014 at a cost of £71 million. The timing of the refit was driven by the mandatory requirement to revalidate the ships safety and environmental certification.</p><p>The decommissioning date of 2018 is the same as that planned at the time of her refit.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-15T16:20:23.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435821/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435821/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435821/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-07","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when HMS Ocean was last refitted; how much that refit cost; and what the intended out-of-service date was stated to be at the time of that refit.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","19048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435822","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-15","<br /><p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (Cm9161), we will enhance a Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carrier to support our amphibious capability. Together with existing amphibious ships of the Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary, this will provide the capacity and capability to deploy our amphibious forces.</p><p>HMS OCEAN can carry up to 690 Embarked Military Forces (EMF) - Royal Marines and Aviation Group personnel - in addition to her ship's company. She can deploy a variety of helicopter types in multiple combinations as required by her mission and role.</p><p>The QEC aircraft carriers can embark up to 900 EMF, in addition to their ship's company, in support of their missions and tasks and a flexible mix of helicopters subject to the operational tasking.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","19050","2015-12-15T16:21:08.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435822/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435822/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435822/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-07","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which individual ships will fulfil the roles currently carried out by HMS Ocean when she is withdrawn from service; and what numbers of (a) amphibious forces and (b) helicopters are carried by (i) HMS Ocean and (ii) the substitute ships.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","19049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435823","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-15","<br /><p>As stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review (Cm9161), we will enhance a Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carrier to support our amphibious capability. Together with existing amphibious ships of the Royal Navy and Royal Fleet Auxiliary, this will provide the capacity and capability to deploy our amphibious forces.</p><p>HMS OCEAN can carry up to 690 Embarked Military Forces (EMF) - Royal Marines and Aviation Group personnel - in addition to her ship's company. She can deploy a variety of helicopter types in multiple combinations as required by her mission and role.</p><p>The QEC aircraft carriers can embark up to 900 EMF, in addition to their ship's company, in support of their missions and tasks and a flexible mix of helicopters subject to the operational tasking.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","19049","2015-12-15T16:21:08.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435823/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435823/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435823/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-07","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which roles currently fulfilled by HMS Ocean will be carried out by HMS Queen Elizabeth and HMS Prince of Wales when they enter service; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","19050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435824","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-15","<p>The expenditure, or planned expenditure, of each Service on television recruitment campaigns in Financial Year (FY) 2015-16 is as follows:</p><p>Naval Service - planned expenditure has not been finalised but is currently forecast to be £4.3 million for Regular personnel and £0.72 million for Reserves.</p><p>Army - planned expenditure is £0.94 million for Regular personnel and £0.65 million for Reserves.</p><p>Royal Air Force (RAF) - planned expenditure has not been finalised but is currently forecast to be £3.46 million. It is not possible to differentiate between Regular and Reserve spend as the majority of RAF advertisements are targeted towards both cadres.</p><p>Plans for expenditure in FY 2016-17 and onwards have not been finalised.</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","18953 ; 18954","2015-12-15T16:22:05.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435824/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435824/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-07","Navy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's planned expenditure is on television recruitment campaigns for the (a) Royal Navy and (b) Royal Navy Reserve in (i) 2015-16, (ii) 2016-17, (iii) 2017-18, (iv) 2018-19 and (v) 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","18952"
