"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435826","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-15","<p>The expenditure, or planned expenditure, of each Service on television recruitment campaigns in Financial Year (FY) 2015-16 is as follows:</p><p>Naval Service - planned expenditure has not been finalised but is currently forecast to be £4.3 million for Regular personnel and £0.72 million for Reserves.</p><p>Army - planned expenditure is £0.94 million for Regular personnel and £0.65 million for Reserves.</p><p>Royal Air Force (RAF) - planned expenditure has not been finalised but is currently forecast to be £3.46 million. It is not possible to differentiate between Regular and Reserve spend as the majority of RAF advertisements are targeted towards both cadres.</p><p>Plans for expenditure in FY 2016-17 and onwards have not been finalised.</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","18952 ; 18953","2015-12-15T16:22:05.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435826/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435826/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-07","Air Force: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's planned expenditure is on television recruitment campaigns for the (a) Royal Air Force and (b) Royal Air Force Reserve in (i) 2015-16, (ii) 2016-17, (iii) 2017-18, (iv) 2018-19 and (v) 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","18954"
