"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435953","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-10","<p><strong></strong></p><p>From January 2015 to August 2015 there have been approximately 75,200 applications made to the Child Maintenance Service.</p><p>6,800 of these were made by former CSA cases affected by reactive case closure, 22,000 were made by former CSA cases affected by proactive case closure and 46,400 were new applications.</p><br /> <br /><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Total Child Maintenance Service applications can be found in table 1 of the Child Maintenance Service 2012 Scheme Experimental Statistics <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-on-the-2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-on-the-2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme</a></li><li>A system issue has been identified which impacts New Application Intake figures. Investigations have been carried out which identified incorrect duplication of New Applications. Figures have been adjusted to account for these duplicates</li><li>Cases have been linked between CSA systems and CMS Systems using the paying and receiving parents national insurance numbers.</li><li>Figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</li></ol>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-10T14:27:45.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435953/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435953/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many monthly Child Maintenance Service new applications from January 2015 were (a) former Child Support Agency (CSA) cases affected by reactive CSA case closure, (b) former CSA cases affective by proactive CSA case closure and (c) other new applications.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","18994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435954","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-10","<p>Information on total number of arrears only cases is not routinely recorded for management information purposes and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-10T14:31:38.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435954/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435954/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of the total Child Maintenance Service caseload at the end of August 2015 were arrears only cases.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","18993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435955","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-10","<p>Work coaches already assess claimants’ situations on a case by case basis. At the initial interview, they discuss Personal Budgeting Support and asses the claimaint’s need for alternative payment arrangements (APA). The work coach maintains an on-going conversation with the claimant at subsequent interviews, to ensure they are happy with the arrangements.</p><p>We have the facility to split payments to members of the household where necessary.</p><p>Work coaches can signpost vulnerable claimants to further help and support where necessary.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-10T15:53:30.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435955/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435955/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his policy to ensure that universal credit claimants are routinely asked if they require the alternative paying arrangement in order to protect vulnerable women and children from experiencing financial abuse.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","19007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435956","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-10","<p>The information requested is not routinely recorded for management information purposes and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-10T14:23:03.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435956/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435956/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of the case groups with a current child maintenance liability within the 2012 statutory child maintenance scheme in August 2015 involve a non-resident parent with (a) one case, (b) two cases, (c) three cases and (d) four or more cases.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","18996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435957","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-10","<p>As at August 2015, 30% of cases paid via the CMS Calculation and Collection Service and 70% of cases paid via Direct Pay.</p><p>Information on Service Type (Case based) is set out on Page 6 of the Child Maintenance Service 2012 Scheme Experimental Statistics and Page 8 of the tables which can be accessed online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme-aug-2013-to-aug-2015-experimental" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme-aug-2013-to-aug-2015-experimental</a></p><br /><p>Note:</p><p>Percentages are rounded to the nearest whole number.</p><br /><p>Accurate information by case group could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-10T14:34:06.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435957/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435957/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of the cases groups with a current liability using the 2012 statutory child maintenance scheme in August 2015 were due to pay via (a) the CMS Calculation and Collection Service and (b) Direct Pay.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","18997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435958","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p>To prevent young people slipping straight into a life on benefits, from April 2017 the Government will remove the automatic entitlement to housing support for new claims in Universal Credit from 18-21 year olds who are out of work. This will ensure young people in the benefits system face the same choices as young people who work and who may not be able to afford to leave home.</p><p>We will ensure that vulnerable young people who are in need of support for their housing needs continue to receive it. Government will consider the impact in line with our legal obligations as part of that process.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:42:07.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435958/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435958/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Housing Benefit: Dundee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many adults under 21 years old in Dundee will be affected by changes to housing benefit.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","19016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435959","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The Government set out its assessment of the impacts of the policies in Bill on 20th July.</p><br /><p>Ministers have considered impacts with regard to all relevant legal obligations when formulating the welfare policies announced in the Bill.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-14T14:40:26.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435959/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435959/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Social Security Benefits: Chronic Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of the measures proposed in clause 13 of the Welfare Reform and Work Bill on claimants with (a) Parkinson's disease and (b) other incurable and degenerative conditions.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","18958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435960","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-18","<p>Information on apprenticeship starts is published as part of a Statistical First Release.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/learner-participation-outcomes-and-level-of-highest-qualification-held" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/learner-participation-outcomes-and-level-of-highest-qualification-held</a></p><br /><p>Latest data show that there were 115,300 apprenticeship starts between 1 May and 31 July 2015.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-18T16:56:15.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435960/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435960/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-07","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many new apprenticeships have been created in the UK since the 2015 general election.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","18963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435961","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>Departmental expenditure on Work Choice contracts to date is £451million. This covers the period from the start of the programme in Financial Year 2010-11 to November 2015.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-14T14:50:07.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435961/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435961/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Employment Schemes: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has spent on the Work Choice programme to date; and what the estimated total cost of that programme over its lifetime is.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435962","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>We have made no proposals to extend Jobseekers Allowance conditionality.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","18912","2015-12-14T14:33:35.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435962/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435962/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Jobseeker's Allowance: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether his Department plans to issue guidance on how its proposed extension of jobseeker's allowance conditionality will apply to claimants with mental illness.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","18911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435963","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-15","<p>The detailed policy design is still under development. We will make further announcements over the coming months as we develop the policy detail.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-15T14:34:22.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435963/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435963/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Employment Schemes: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 27 October 2015 to Question 12462, when he expects to announce further policy details of the Youth Obligation.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435964","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-10","<p>DWP Ministers have visited a number of third sector organisations, faith groups, civil society organisations and charities, including food banks since May 2010.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-10T15:39:20.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435964/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435964/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will list the (a) location and (b) dates of visits he has made to food banks since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","18925"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435965","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>We have made no proposals to extend Jobseekers Allowance conditionality.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","18911","2015-12-14T14:33:35.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435965/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435965/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Jobseeker's Allowance: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on claimants with mental illness of his proposals to extend jobseeker's allowance conditionality.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","18912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435966","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>We are aligning treatment of temporary absences from Great Britain in housing benefit with the current treatment in Universal Credit.</p><br /><p>We plan to make a number of easements for people in work, including for members of the armed forces, mariners and continental shelf workers.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:42:10.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435966/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435966/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Housing Benefit: Overseas Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the proposed reduction in the maximum length of time for which housing benefit is payable for tenants travelling overseas on claimants required by their employers to work overseas for extended periods; and what exemptions he plans to put in place to protect claimants in such circumstances.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435967","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The existing exemptions that already apply to private rented sector tenants will be carefully considered prior to implementing the Local Housing Allowance cap for tenants living in the social rented sector.</p><p>It should be noted that the policy applies from April 2018, but only where new tenancies have been taken out or renewed after April 2016.</p><p>The Discretionary Housing Payment scheme will be available to Local Authorities to protect the vulnerable.</p><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-12-14T16:49:04.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435967/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435967/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, what exemptions he plans to put in place to protect vulnerable households from restrictions to housing benefit in the social sector.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","18839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435968","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>As announced in the Spending Review, the Government will publish a White Paper in 2016 that will set out reforms to improve support for people with health conditions and disabilities.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel","18796","2015-12-14T14:28:46.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435968/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435968/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Employment Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to publish the White Paper on supporting people with health conditions and disabilities to get into work.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","18845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435969","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-15","<p>The Department took its obligations under the Equality Act 2010 into account when making changes to the WCA handbook and recognises it has an on-going equality duty under the Act and is committed to complying with this duty.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-15T14:26:56.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435969/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435969/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on women with a mental function problem of the different assessment recommended for them in its Work Capability Assessment handbook on risk of self-harm, suicide or other risk.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","18863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435970","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The information available is in the table below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>As at May 2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Work Related Activity Group</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Caseload (Thousands)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Mental and Behavioural Disorders</strong></p></td><td><p>240.64</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><strong>Notes:</strong></p><br /><p>The extract is as at May 2015 which is the latest data available.</p><br /><p><strong>Source:</strong></p><br /><p>DWP Tabulation Tool <a href="http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/100pc/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/100pc/tabtool.html</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-14T15:16:30.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435970/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435970/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people receive employment and support allowance in the work-related activity group on grounds of mental or behavioural disorders.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","18860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435971","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The Department published its strategy for releasing official statistics on Universal Credit in September 2013. As outlined in the strategy, officials are quality assuring data for Universal Credit and formulating a definitive list of what statistics will be provided in the future.</p><br /><p>These statistics will be published in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-14T15:08:28.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435971/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435971/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Universal Credit: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether he plans to publish statistics on sanctions imposed under the universal credit scheme during the course of its implementation.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","18861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435972","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-14","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><br /><p>The latest Jobseeker’s Allowance and Employment and Support Allowance sanctions statistics can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/jobseekers-allowance-sanctions</a></p><br /> <br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-12-14T14:46:17.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435972/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/435972/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-07","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of (a) jobseeker's allowance and (b) employment and support allowance claims were subject to a sanction (i) pre-challenge and (ii) post-challenge in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","18862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436908","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-10","<p><strong>Consumers must be able to trust data provided to inform their purchasing decisions. That is why the government pushed in Europe for the recently agreed changes to the way emissions are measured. </strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong>I am pleased that real driving emissions will be measured from 2017 but, in the meantime, officials are retesting the emission performance of the most popular vehicles in Great Britain. We will publish a report of this work in spring 2016.</strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-12-10T15:17:15.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436908/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436908/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-07","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that consumers can have confidence in vehicle emissions data.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","902646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436909","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-10","<p><strong>In our manifesto we committed to improve compensation for delayed rail passengers. We have already changed the system to get compensation paid in cash, not travel vouchers, and we are putting new compensation obligations like automatic delay/repay into franchise specifications.</strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong>We will negotiate hard with rail operators to get even better compensation arrangements for passengers but also focus on what we all want which is to have the trains run on time.</strong></p><br /> <br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-12-10T15:26:13.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436909/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436909/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-07","Railways: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to improve the passenger compensation regime for train delays and cancellations.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","902651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436910","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-10","<br /><p>The Secretary of State for Transport’s written statement of 10 Nov 2015 advised that the programme was underway and that he would keep the House informed of progress.</p><br /><p>The Vehicle Certification Agency has tested 7 independently sourced vehicles at a commercial laboratory. Two more laboratories will increase the volume of tests in the New Year. We intend to test approximately 40 vehicles and a report will be published next spring.</p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-12-10T16:32:15.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436910/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436910/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-07","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made on the motor vehicle emissions retesting programme.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","902647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436911","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Government is currently committed to exploring the sale of its 49% shareholding in NATS and maximise returns to the taxpayer.</p><br /><p>We have not yet set a timetable for the sale.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-12-10T15:33:53.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436911/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/436911/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-12-07","National Air Traffic Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what timetable the Government plans to follow for the proposed sale of its share in NATS.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","902648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434187","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-09","<p>We have taken significant steps to widen participation in higher education. In particular, from 2015/16, we have removed the cap on student numbers, enabling more people than ever before to benefit from higher education. We have also established a stronger framework with increased responsibility placed on providers to widen access. The Director of Fair Access has agreed 183 Access Agreements for 2016/17 containing an estimated £745m to support students from disadvantaged backgrounds – up from £404m in 2009/10.</p><br /><p>The Green Paper <em>Fulfilling our Potential: Teaching Excellence, Social Mobility and Student Choice, CM 9141 </em>sets out additional steps the Government plans to take to increase the proportion of students from disadvantaged background entering higher education including through the new guidance that we plan to issue to the Director of Fair Access, and through the social mobility taskforce being set up by Universities UK.</p><br /><p>We will work with the Higher Education Funding Council for England to target the Student Opportunity Fund in the most effective way and with the Director of Fair Access to ensure that universities take more responsibility for widening access, prioritising activities that demonstrate the greatest value for money.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","18813","2015-12-09T10:04:05.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434187/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434187/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Higher Education: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect of recent changes to the student opportunity fund on the number of people from disadvantaged backgrounds entering higher education.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","18779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434188","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-14","<p>In the last 12 months, UK Trade and Investment (UKTI) has organised the following trade missions to Latin America;</p><p>Multi-Sector Mission to Colombia and Peru – November 2014</p><p>Multi-Sector Mission to Mexico and Colombia – November/December 2014</p><p>Automotive Mission to Mexico - December 2014</p><p>Oil &amp; Gas Mission to Colombia - March 2015</p><p>Trade Mission to Mexico – March 2015</p><p>Trade Mission to Brazil – March 2015</p><p>Global Sports Mission to Brazil - August 2015</p><p>Northern PowerHouse Mission to Mexico/Colombia – September/October 2015</p><p>Water Mission to Brazil (visiting FITABES Trade Show) – October 2015</p><p>MSB (Medium Size Business) to Brazil (led by Lord Maude) – November 2015</p><p>Broadcast Mission to Mexico – November 2015</p><p>Multi- Sector Mission to Colombia and Peru – November 2015</p><p>Information relating to planned missions from April 2016 onwards is not available at this time. UKTI is currently undertaking business planning for the period in question. The 2016-2017 Events Programme will be available by end of March 2016.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-14T11:26:57.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434188/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434188/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Trade Missions: Latin America","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what trade missions to Latin America the Government has organised in the last 12 months; and what such trade missions are planned in the next 12 months.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","18792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434189","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-15","<br /><p>Interest rates on student loans vary according to a number of factors, including a borrower's level of earnings, and whether they remain in contact with the Student Loans Company to ensure they are repaying when they are eligible to do so.</p><br /><p>The maximum interest rate for the post-2012 system is the Retail Price Index (RPI) figure plus 3%. The maximum rate applies whilst the borrower is studying; is the maximum interest rate for those borrowers earning £41,000 and over; and is the default interest rate for those borrowers who fail to keep in touch with the Student Loans Company.</p><br /><p>Once a borrower is due to repay, a variable rate of interest will be charged, which is dependent upon income. Borrowers with an income of £21,000 or less will accrue interest at RPI. For a borrower with income greater than £21,000, a real rate of interest will be tapered in, reaching a maximum of RPI plus 3% at an income of £41,000 or more.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-12-15T17:03:01.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434189/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434189/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the rationale is for setting the interest rate on the repayment of student loans under the new system at three per cent.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","18798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434190","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-09","<p>We have taken significant steps to widen participation in higher education. In particular, from 2015/16, we have removed the cap on student numbers, enabling more people than ever before to benefit from higher education. We have also established a stronger framework with increased responsibility placed on providers to widen access. The Director of Fair Access has agreed 183 Access Agreements for 2016/17 containing an estimated £745m to support students from disadvantaged backgrounds – up from £404m in 2009/10.</p><br /><p>The Green Paper <em>Fulfilling our Potential: Teaching Excellence, Social Mobility and Student Choice, CM 9141 </em>sets out additional steps the Government plans to take to increase the proportion of students from disadvantaged background entering higher education including through the new guidance that we plan to issue to the Director of Fair Access, and through the social mobility taskforce being set up by Universities UK.</p><br /><p>We will work with the Higher Education Funding Council for England to target the Student Opportunity Fund in the most effective way and with the Director of Fair Access to ensure that universities take more responsibility for widening access, prioritising activities that demonstrate the greatest value for money.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","18779","2015-12-09T10:04:05.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434190/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434190/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Higher Education: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what progress his Department is making on doubling the proportion of people from disadvantaged backgrounds entering higher education by 2020.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","18813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434191","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-09","<p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>Apprenticeship starts by academic year and the framework of the apprenticeship is published at the FE data library (first link) as a supplementary table to a Statistical First Release (second link):</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a></p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/477738/apprenticeships-starts-by-sase-framework.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/477738/apprenticeships-starts-by-sase-framework.xls</a></p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-12-09T18:02:14.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434191/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434191/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many apprenticeships were available in the (a) food and (b) tourism sectors in (i) 2010 and (ii) 2015.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434192","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Spending Review set out the allocation of the Joint Security Fund for the Ministry of Defence and the Intelligence Agencies totalling £3.5bn over 5 years.</p><br /><p>The Joint Security Fund will be used to deliver the investments set out in the Strategic Defence and Security Review. The allocation of funding is conditional on annual spending limits that were agreed at the Spending Review. As with all public expenditure, Managing Public Money sets out how public funds must be spent, including the principles of regularity and propriety.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-12-10T17:17:43.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434192/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434192/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-04","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what conditionality is attached to disbursements from the Joint Security Fund; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434193","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-10","<p>The full list of successful Enterprise Zones, which is available to view online, was published by the Department of Communities and Local Government following the Spending Review announcement.</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/news/the-new-enterprise-zones" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/news/the-new-enterprise-zones</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-12-10T17:22:47.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434193/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434193/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-04","Enterprise Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) rural and (b) urban areas designated enterprise zones in the most recent round of bidding.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434194","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-09","<p>Our intention is to deliver an application route for permission in principle as soon as possible after receiving Royal Assent to the enabling powers in the Housing and Planning Bill and laying the associated secondary legislation on the detailed procedures.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-12-09T17:13:20.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434194/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434194/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-04","Planning Permission: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the publication, Towards a one nation economy: A 10-point plan for boosting rural productivity, published in August 2015, when he plans that the fast-track planning certificate process will be available.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434195","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","<p>The Prime Minister's excellent announcement to give people a legal right to request a connection to broadband with speeds of 10 Mbps, no matter where in the country they live through a new broadband Universal Service Obligation (USO)followed reports of consumers' broadband needs from a range of sources, including Ofcom's annual infrastructure reports.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T16:15:50.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434195/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434195/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-04","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment the Government undertook of consumer needs before announcing its plan to introduce a 10Mbps universal broadband speed.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434196","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","<p>Following the Government's landmark agreement with mobile network operators in December 2014 and the 4G licence obligation on Telefonica we expect mobile coverage to improve significantly - with coverage to nearly 98% of UK landmass by 2017.In August 2015 Ofcom published an online interactive map showing areas of mobile coverage in the UK. The map is available at:<a href="http://www.ofcom.org.uk/mobile-coverage" target="_blank">http://www.ofcom.org.uk/mobile-coverage</a>. No such map exists for coverage in 2010.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T16:21:45.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434196/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434196/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-04","Mobile Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which areas of the UK had (a) limited and (b) no mobile coverage in (i) 2010 and (ii) 2015.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434197","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Government remains committed to delivering a reformed Electronic Communications Code that is clear, fit for purpose, and supports improvements in network coverage which provides consumers with a choice of high quality telecommunications services. We will update Parliament on plans in due course.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-10T16:29:51.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434197/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434197/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-04","Telecommunications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 20 July 2015 to Question 6371, when he plans that the reforms to the Electronic Communications Code will come into effect; if he will ensure that the new Code contains powers for mobile operators to more easily upgrade and share sites; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","18825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434198","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-11","<p>According to Ofcom’s Connected Nations Report 2015, published on 1 December 2015, superfast broadband coverageis now available to 68% of small and medium businesses (SMEs) - up from 56% last year– a very substantial increase.</p><p>In addition, the £40 million government-funded Broadband Connection Voucher Schemehas benefitted well over 50,000 SMEs,who employ up to 1 million people across the UK; and we are on track to hit 95% superfast broadband coverage across the UK by 2017. In addition, the PM recently announced the ambition to give people the legal right to request a connection to broadband with speeds of 10 Mbps, no matter where in the country they live.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-11T16:18:34.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434198/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434198/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-04","Broadband: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of the proportion of UK businesses that do not have access to broadband with speeds above 24Mbps.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434199","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-14","<br /><p>The information requested for the Naval Service, as at 1 August 2015, is provided in the tables below. This is also available in the Royal Navy and Royal Marines Monthly Personnel Situation Report for August 2015, published on the GOV.UK website at the following link:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/458873/20150907_RN_RM_Situation_Report_rounded_August2015.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/458873/20150907_RN_RM_Situation_Report_rounded_August2015.pdf</a></p><br /><p><strong>Regular Royal Navy and Royal Marines Officer Strength by Paid Rank</strong></p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Rear Admiral/Major General and Above</p></td><td><p>Commodore/ Brigadier</p></td><td><p>Captain RN/ Colonel</p></td><td><p>Commander/Lieutenant Colonel</p></td><td><p>Lieutenant Commander/Major</p></td><td><p>Lieutenant/ Captain RM</p></td><td><p>Sub- Lieutenant/ Lieutenant/ 2<sup>nd</sup> Lieutenant</p></td><td><p>Officer Designate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>80</p></td><td><p>290</p></td><td><p>1,060</p></td><td><p>2,000</p></td><td><p>2,510</p></td><td><p>750</p></td><td><p>170</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><strong>Regular Royal Navy and Royal Marines Ratings Strength by Paid Rank</strong></p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Warrant Officer 1</p></td><td><p>Warrant Officer 2</p></td><td><p>Chief Petty Officer/Colour Sergeant</p></td><td><p>Petty Officer/ Sergeant</p></td><td><p>Leading Rate/ Corporal</p></td><td><p>Lance Corporal</p></td><td><p>Able Rate/ Marine</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>910</p></td><td><p>460</p></td><td><p>3,040</p></td><td><p>3,640</p></td><td><p>5,580</p></td><td><p>720</p></td><td><p>11,970</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Note:</p><br /><p>All totals are rounded in accordance with the Defence Statistics rounding policy; therefore totals may not equal the sum of their parts. All numbers are rounded to the nearest 10 with numbers ending in 5 rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to avoid bias. Figures include Trained, Untrained and Full Time Reserves Service personnel.</p><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-14T16:10:03.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434199/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434199/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Naval officers and ratings at each rank were employed by the Royal Navy on 31 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","18819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434200","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-14","<p>Time spent at sea can vary depending on the tasking of the vessel.</p><p>The information requested is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-14T16:14:11.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434200/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434200/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Navy: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many days on average each class of Royal Naval officer and rating was at sea in each year between 2005 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","18818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434201","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-14","<br /><p>Information on RAF airstrikes in Iraq and Syria, and their outcome, is already published on the gov.uk website and is regularly updated. We know of no civilian casualties caused by RAF airstrikes against Daesh in Iraq or Syria.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-14T16:11:43.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434201/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434201/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish on his Department's website (a) corroborated information on deaths of (i) ISIS fighters and (ii) civilians as a result of airstrikes on Syrian locations and (b) other information in a daily battle assessment for each day from 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434202","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence plans to retain all receipts from the sale of land and property assets.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-12-14T16:14:50.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434202/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434202/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Ministry of Defence: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department plans to retain or to return to the Consolidated Fund receipts from the sale of land and property assets over the Spending Review period.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434203","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Ministry of Defence will be able to spend £2.1 billion from the Joint Security Fund over the rest of this Parliament. The annual profile is subject to formal confirmation of the Chancellor's settlement for defence expected later this month.</p><p>Use of the Joint Security Fund by the Security and Intelligence Agencies is a matter for the Cabinet Office.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-12-10T17:28:31.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434203/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434203/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the planned schedule of disbursements from the Joint Security Fund is for (a) his Department and (b) the security and intelligence agencies in each year from 2016-17 to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434204","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-09","<p>The information used to identify and strike targets is derived from a number of different sources and assessed rigorously for compliance with UK rules of engagement, UK law and international law. It is not our practice to comment in detail on how specific operational targets are derived, as to do so would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-09T16:16:47.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434204/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434204/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether it is planned that RAF pilots will rely upon information provided by personnel on the ground to identify and attack targets territory in Syria occupied by ISIS.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434205","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-11","<p>I am withholding details of costs for in-service Paveway IV bombs and Brimstone missiles as disclosure would prejudice commercial interests. I am also withholding details of the number of bombs and missiles held by the RAF as disclosure would or would likely prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of our Armed Forces and allies.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-12-11T14:28:02.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434205/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434205/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-04","Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost is of each (a) Paveway IV bomb and (b) Brimstone missile procured by the RAF; and how many such weapons are in the RAF stockpile.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434206","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>Information on the total entries for GCSEs in Spanish is published at national level as part of the “GCSE and equivalent results in England” statistical first release [1]<sup>,[2],[3],[4],[5]</sup></p><br /><p>[1] 2014/15 provisional table can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/467610/SFR37_2015_Subject_Timeseries.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/467610/SFR37_2015_Subject_Timeseries.xls</a>. (Years: 2009/10 - 2014/15)</p><p>[2] 2008/09 revised table 8 can be found at: <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00196306/ks4-results-in-england-2008-09-(revised)" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00196306/ks4-results-in-england-2008-09-(revised)</a>. (Year: 2008/09)</p><p>[3] 2007/08 revised table 10 can be found at: <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00195931/gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00195931/gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england</a>. (Year: 2007/08)</p><p>[4] 2006/07 revised table 10 can be found at: <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00195692/dcsf-gcse-and-equivalent-examination-results-in-en" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00195692/dcsf-gcse-and-equivalent-examination-results-in-en</a>. (Year: 2006/07)</p><p>[5] 2005/06 revised table 10 can be found at: <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00195387/gcse-and-equivalent-examination-results-in-england" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20130401151655/http:/www.education.gov.uk/researchandstatistics/statistics/allstatistics/a00195387/gcse-and-equivalent-examination-results-in-england</a>. (Year: 2005/06)</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-12-09T15:28:25.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434206/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434206/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-04","Spanish Language: GCSE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many pupils took a GCSE in Spanish in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","18794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434207","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>Since September 2014, maintained primary schools in England must teach a modern or ancient foreign language to pupils at key stage 2 (ages 7 to 11). According to the annual language trends surveys conducted by the Centre for British Teachers, 20 per cent of primary schools taught Spanish in 2014, up from 16 per cent in 2012. In order to support the new curriculum, the government is funding nine projects across the country providing continued professional development for primary and secondary teachers, including training and resources for the teaching of Spanish.</p><br /><p>The government took action in 2010 to halt the decline in the number of school children taking language GCSEs by introducing the English Baccalaureate. This has had a positive effect on the take up of languages in schools. The proportion of the cohort in state funded schools entered for a modern foreign language has risen from 40 per cent in 2010 to 49 per cent in 2015. Over the same period, there has been a 46 per cent rise in the number of entries for Spanish GCSE in schools in England.</p><br /><p>The government’s goal is that, in time, at least 90 per cent of pupils enter GCSEs in the EBacc subjects of English, maths, science, humanities and languages.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-12-09T17:06:46.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434207/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434207/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-04","Spanish Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans the Government has to increase the number of students studying Spanish in schools.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","18795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434208","Department for Education","false","2015-12-10","<p>Savings of £600 million will be made by reducing the Education Services Grant (ESG), including phasing out the additional funding that goes to schools and local authorities. We will be making a small efficiency saving (around £80 million) from the ESG in 2016-17, and will be setting out our proposals for savings from 2017-18 in the New Year. This will include consulting on the details of the statutory duties that will be removed.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","18810","2015-12-10T12:46:19.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434208/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434208/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-04","Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to paragraph 2.64 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, which education-related statutory duties on local authorities she plans to remove; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434209","Department for Education","false","2015-12-10","<p>Savings of £600 million will be made by reducing the Education Services Grant (ESG), including phasing out the additional funding that goes to schools and local authorities. We will be making a small efficiency saving (around £80 million) from the ESG in 2016-17, and will be setting out our proposals for savings from 2017-18 in the New Year. This will include consulting on the details of the statutory duties that will be removed.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","18809","2015-12-10T12:46:19.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434209/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434209/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-04","Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to paragraph 2.64 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, how she plans to make £600 million savings from the Education Services Grant; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434210","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>The government is committed to delivering our manifesto pledge to make school funding fairer. It was announced at the Spending Review that we intend to introduce a National Funding Formula for schools, high needs and early years in 2017. We will set out our detailed plans for a National Funding Formula, including the criteria to be included in the formula for schools, in the New Year and will consult on our proposals extensively.</p><br /><br />","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2015-12-08T14:35:37.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434210/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434210/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-04","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what criteria she plans to include in the national funding formula for schools; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434211","Department for Education","false","2015-12-11","<p>The government provides local authorities and other bodies responsible for school buildings with capital funding for schools through condition funding and basic need funding for new school places. Local authorities can spend this money on new school buildings but the department does not collect the data centrally on the number of new school buildings. Information on the impact of this funding in each local authority and parliamentary constituency could therefore be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><br /><p>The government does directly deliver new schools, in new or refurbished buildings, through the Free Schools, University Technical Colleges and Studio Schools programmes. There are currently 383 schools that are open through these programmes.</p><br /><p>A list of all open free schools can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-open-schools-and-successful-applications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/free-schools-open-schools-and-successful-applications</a>.</p><p>A list of all open University Technical Colleges and Studio Schools can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/utcs-and-studio-schools-open-schools-and-applications-received" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/utcs-and-studio-schools-open-schools-and-applications-received</a>.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-12-11T13:31:48.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434211/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434211/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-04","Schools: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many new schools were built in each local education authority area between 1997 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434212","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Government set out its capital budget and priorities for this Spending Review period on 25 November 2015.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:35:44.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434212/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434212/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Carbon Capture and Storage: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how she plans to account for the £1 billion of carbon capture and storage support reallocated at the Spending Review 2015 within her Departmental budget; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","18774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434213","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Foreign Secretary’s Special Representative on Climate Change attended the event and spoke on a panel event entitled “what is most needed to embed innovation across public and private sector operations.”</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:36:23.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434213/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434213/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Climate Change Convention: Paris","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what participation the UK has had in the sustainable innovation forum hosted by the UN Environment Programme as part of the COP21 climate change conference in Paris.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434214","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The framework for civil nuclear safety and security is kept under continuous review to ensure that it remains robust, effective and of an appropriate standard.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:36:40.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434214/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434214/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Nuclear Power: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether she plans to issue revised nuclear safety and security regulations.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434215","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Government set out its capital budget and priorities for this Spending Review period on 25 November 2015.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:37:57.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434215/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434215/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434215/answer/previousversion/34703","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Carbon Capture and Storage: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, to what purposes the ring-fenced capital budget for the carbon capture and storage competition has been reallocated.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434216","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-15","<p>The Department takes into account a number of factors to project Levy Control Framework (LCF) spending in relation to Contracts for Difference (CfD) contracts, including capacity for each individual project, strike prices, wholesale electricity prices, load factors and commissioning dates. Some of the CfD predictions that fed into the Office for Budget Responsibility November LCF forecasts are already in the public domain, such as strike prices for signed CfD contracts which are available on the LCCC website. Some predictions are based on commercial intelligence and sensitive information from the developers which we cannot disclose.</p><p><br></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-15T15:28:19.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434216/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434216/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Electricity Generation: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assumptions her Department relied on to produce the information on expenditure on Contracts for Difference in respect of each eligible technology that it provided to inform the Office for Budget Responsibility assessment of the Levy Control Framework.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434217","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI) does not operate under separate budgets for the domestic and non-domestic schemes. For 2015/16 it has a single budget limit of £430m for both schemes combined. This is a spending limit, not a central forecast; and the scheme is not deemed to have ‘underspent’ if expenditure is below that limit. The central spend forecast for 2015/16 that was set out at the time the £430m budget limit was agreed (as part of the 2013 Spending Round) was £365m.</p><br /><p>DECC does not regularly publish forecast expenditure for financial years; instead publishing monthly data on ‘committed expenditure’ – the estimated costs of supporting all plants applied to the scheme for a rolling 12-month cycle.</p><br /><p>However, as part of the 2015 Comprehensive Spending Review, the Office of Budget Responsibility (OBR) have published a forecast of £420m for 15/16:</p><br /><p><a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/supplementary-forecast-information/" target="_blank">http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/supplementary-forecast-information/</a>.</p><br /><p>This is still subject to considerable uncertainty, as the scheme is largely paid on metered heat; and so final expenditure will be determined by the level of heat generation this winter, as well as rates of new applications.</p><br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-09T17:10:00.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434217/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434217/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Renewable Energy: Heating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what forecast her Department has made of the level of potential underspend on the (a) domestic and (b) non-domestic Renewable Heat Incentive in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434218","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Department is currently considering the Committee on Climate Change’s advice and Government will set the fifth carbon budget in law next year.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:37:07.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434218/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434218/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434218/answer/previousversion/34702","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps her Department is taking in response to the recommendations of the Committee on Climate Change on carbon capture storage and the power sector in its report, Power scenarios for the fifth carbon budget, published in October 2015.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434219","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-14","<p>These are requirements under European Law. There are no plans to review the assessment principles on imperative reasons of overriding public interest in big energy planning projects.</p><br /> <br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-14T14:56:04.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434219/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434219/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Energy: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether she plans to review the assessment principles on imperative reasons of overriding public interest in big energy planning projects.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434220","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-14","<p>A report<sup>1</sup> published by the Department of Business, Innovation &amp; Skills estimated that the Carbon Capture and Storage sector and supply chain contributed £200m of Gross Value Added to the UK economy in 2013. The Government has not made a recent estimate of the potential annual value of the CCS industry to the UK economy by 2020.</p><p><br></p><p><em><sup>1</sup> The size and performance of the UK low carbon economy, BIS, March 2015.</em></p><p><em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416240/bis-15-206-size-and-performance-of-uk-low-carbon-economy.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/416240/bis-15-206-size-and-performance-of-uk-low-carbon-economy.pdf</a></em></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-14T15:01:50.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434220/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434220/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-04","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent estimate the Government has made of the potential annual value of the carbon capture and storage industry to the UK economy by 2020.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434221","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-10","<p>Overall, the phosphate levels in Hertfordshire’s rivers have remained stable over the past 12 months. Phosphate can remain present in river sediments for a number of years, and it can take five to 10 years to show any signs of ecological recovery following phosphate reductions.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-12-10T15:14:45.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434221/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434221/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-04","Rivers: Hertfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 2734, what changes to phosphate pollution levels in Hertfordshire's chalk rivers have been recorded over the past 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","18833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434222","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-14","<p>The planned budgets (2016/17 to 2020/21) and locations of the four Centres for Agricultural Innovation are:</p><p><strong>Centre for Crop Health and Protection (CHAP)</strong> - headquarters in York at the National AgriFood Innovation Campus in Sand Hutton</p><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><p><strong>16/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>17/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>18/19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>19/20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>20/21</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£m</p></td><td><p>6.5</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td><td><p>4.4</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><strong>Centre for Innovation Excellence in Livestock (CIEL)</strong> - headquarters in York at the National AgriFood Innovation Campus in Sand Hutton</p><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><p><strong>16/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>17/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>18/19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>19/20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>20/21</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£m</p></td><td><p>8.6</p></td><td><p>6.0</p></td><td><p>4.5</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><strong>Agricultural Engineering Precision Innovation Centre (Agri-EPI)</strong> - hubs in Edinburgh, Harper Adams University (Shropshire) and Cranfield University (Bedfordshire)</p><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><p><strong>16/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>17/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>18/19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>19/20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>20/21</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£m</p></td><td><p>5.3</p></td><td><p>3.6</p></td><td><p>3.0</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><strong>Centre for Agricultural Informatics (Agrimetrics)</strong> - headquarters in Harpenden (Hertfordshire) at Rothamsted Research</p><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><p><strong>16/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>17/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>18/19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>19/20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>20/21</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£m</p></td><td><p>3.2</p></td><td><p>2.9</p></td><td><p>1.8</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td><td><p>0.0</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-14T11:28:08.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434222/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434222/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Agriculture: Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the (a) location and (b) budget is for each agri-tech centre in each year from 2016-17 to 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434223","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-09","<p>The payment window for the Basic Payment Scheme 2015 runs between 1st December 2015 and 30th June 2016.</p><br /><p>We received around 88,000 Basic Payment Scheme applications for 2015. On the 1st December, the opening of the Basic Payment Scheme 2015 payment window, we paid around 33,000 claims. This means that, as a proportion, around 62% of claims are still being processed.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","18781","2015-12-09T10:25:20.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434223/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434223/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of single farm payment and basic payment claims to the Rural Payments Agency are outstanding.","false","Biography information for Dr Liam Fox","North Somerset","Dr Liam Fox","18780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434224","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-09","<p>The payment window for the Basic Payment Scheme 2015 runs between 1st December 2015 and 30th June 2016.</p><br /><p>We received around 88,000 Basic Payment Scheme applications for 2015. On the 1st December, the opening of the Basic Payment Scheme 2015 payment window, we paid around 33,000 claims. This means that, as a proportion, around 62% of claims are still being processed.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","18780","2015-12-09T10:25:21.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434224/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434224/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-04","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when the payment window for the single farm payment and basic payment will open.","false","Biography information for Dr Liam Fox","North Somerset","Dr Liam Fox","18781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434225","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Government sees the contribution of UK agriculture as vital to our food security. A detailed analysis of the global and domestic factors affecting UK food security, the UK Food Security Assessment, was published in 2010 and refreshed in 2012. Its main conclusion was that UK food security depends on a combination of a strong domestic food production base and access to a wide variety of world markets. The assessment also analysed the impact of extreme scenarios and concluded that if necessary the UK could feed itself from domestic resources.</p><p>The Government is working on a 25 Year Plan for Food and Farming which will set out ways our domestic food production base can be further strengthened, building on the Great British brand.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-12-09T10:14:55.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434225/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434225/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-04","Food Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether food security is part of the Government's agricultural planning; and what assessment her Department has made of the amount of farmland required to guarantee food supplies in a time of crisis.","false","Biography information for Dr Liam Fox","North Somerset","Dr Liam Fox","18807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434226","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office travel advice provides information and advice so that British nationals can make their own better informed decisions about foreign travel. The Department for Business Innovation and Skills is responsible for regulation of the travel industry and it is not the role of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office to intervene in the regulation of this market. British nationals who have booked package holidays should contact their travel company if they wish to cancel their booking. These holidays will be subject to the terms and conditions of the booking and the provisions of the Package Travel Regulations, which cover among other things changes between the time of booking and the time of travel. Where the Foreign and Commonwealth Office has advised against travel since a holiday has been booked, such as Sharm el Sheikh, it is unlikely that a penalty will be incurred.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-12-09T14:36:03.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434226/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434226/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","Middle East: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will assess the expected cost to UK consumers who elect to cancel booked package holidays to Sharm el Sheikh and other destinations in the Middle East scheduled to depart during the months of December 2015 and January 2016 where such cancellation is not penalty-free; and if he will make it his Department's policy to issue travel advice which will allow penalty-free cancellation for travel booked to depart during those months.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mike Weir","18806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434227","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-15","<p>The UNESCO Institute of Statistics estimates for every country the number of outbound tertiary students studying in different regions of the world. Their most recent figures refer to 2013 and are published at the link: <a href="http://data.uis.unesco.org/" target="_blank">http://data.uis.unesco.org/</a></p><p>The estimated number of UK students attending universities in Latin America and the Caribbean in 2013 was 234.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-12-15T14:52:23.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434227/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434227/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-04","Latin America: Foreign Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many UK students attend universities in Latin America.","false","Biography information for Graham Stuart","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","18793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434228","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-14","<p>The UK enjoys a strong and constructive relationship with Bahrain where we are able to raise and discuss issues such as the revocation of citizenship of Bahraini nationals. This is often at Ministerial level or through our wider human rights and reform dialogue. We will continue to encourage the Government of Bahrain to ensure that the appeals process is fair and transparent.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-12-14T15:37:19.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434228/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434228/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","Bahrain: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what effect the practice of revoking citizenship from protestors by the Bahraini government has had on UK policy towards that country.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","18775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434229","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>On 4 November 2015, we amended our Travel Advice to advise against all but essential travel by air to Sharm el-Sheikh. We have not changed our Travel Advice for the resort itself.</p><p>The FCO Travel Advice, available at www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice, provides objective information and advice to help individuals make better-informed decisions about their travel. The Egypt page has been regularly updated to reflect developing events since the crash of the Russian airliner on 31 October. We regularly review our Travel Advice and all changes are made after careful analysis. Our only consideration is the safety of British Nationals.</p><p>The FCO is working with DfT and Egyptian counterparts to put in place permanent and sustainable measures to allow British flights to Sharm el-Sheikh to resume as soon as possible.</p><p>Refunds and cancellation penalties are a matter for the airlines. We are liaising closely with airlines to share information about the progress of our discussions with Egypt.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","18803 ; 18804","2015-12-09T14:39:32.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434229/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434229/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","Egypt: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he plans to issue revised travel advice for visitors from the UK with bookings for package holidays in Egypt departing in the next six weeks which use (a) the airport and (b) the resort at Sharm el Sheikh.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mike Weir","18802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434230","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>On 4 November 2015, we amended our Travel Advice to advise against all but essential travel by air to Sharm el-Sheikh. We have not changed our Travel Advice for the resort itself.</p><p>The FCO Travel Advice, available at www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice, provides objective information and advice to help individuals make better-informed decisions about their travel. The Egypt page has been regularly updated to reflect developing events since the crash of the Russian airliner on 31 October. We regularly review our Travel Advice and all changes are made after careful analysis. Our only consideration is the safety of British Nationals.</p><p>The FCO is working with DfT and Egyptian counterparts to put in place permanent and sustainable measures to allow British flights to Sharm el-Sheikh to resume as soon as possible.</p><p>Refunds and cancellation penalties are a matter for the airlines. We are liaising closely with airlines to share information about the progress of our discussions with Egypt.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","18802 ; 18804","2015-12-09T14:39:32.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434230/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434230/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","Egypt: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will extend the validity period of travel advice applying to Sharm el Sheikh to provide certainty on the right to penalty-free cancellation (a) six weeks and (b) four weeks prior to departure.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mike Weir","18803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434231","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>On 4 November 2015, we amended our Travel Advice to advise against all but essential travel by air to Sharm el-Sheikh. We have not changed our Travel Advice for the resort itself.</p><p>The FCO Travel Advice, available at www.gov.uk/foreign-travel-advice, provides objective information and advice to help individuals make better-informed decisions about their travel. The Egypt page has been regularly updated to reflect developing events since the crash of the Russian airliner on 31 October. We regularly review our Travel Advice and all changes are made after careful analysis. Our only consideration is the safety of British Nationals.</p><p>The FCO is working with DfT and Egyptian counterparts to put in place permanent and sustainable measures to allow British flights to Sharm el-Sheikh to resume as soon as possible.</p><p>Refunds and cancellation penalties are a matter for the airlines. We are liaising closely with airlines to share information about the progress of our discussions with Egypt.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","18802 ; 18803","2015-12-09T14:39:32.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434231/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434231/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","Middle East: Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effect on travellers with bookings to (a) Sharm el Sheikh and (b) other destinations in the Middle East of the period within which the right to penalty-free cancellation can be ascertained being within 14 days of travel.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mike Weir","18804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434232","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office issues travel advice to help British nationals make their own informed decisions about foreign travel. We keep our travel advice under constant review and will update it according to any changes in our assessment of the threat to British nationals around the world. Although the Foreign and Commonwealth Office maintains a dialogue with Association of British Travel Agents about how the travel advice affects their members’ business, it is not the role of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office to intervene in the regulation of the market by discussing changes to the rules applying to penalty-free cancellation.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-12-09T16:07:54.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434232/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434232/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","Travel Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will meet representatives of the Association of British Travel Agents and consumer groups to discuss changes to rules applying to penalty-free cancellation during periods of regional airstrikes by British forces.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mike Weir","18805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434233","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-14","<p>The Government and Overseas Territories committed at the Joint Ministerial Council to work in partnership as appropriate to support capacity building and the development of expertise in public financial management and economic planning. This includes maintaining sound public finances, building economic resilience and ensuring value for money in use of public funds, including through effective use of audit.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-12-14T16:34:32.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434233/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434233/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-04","British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proposals the Government made aimed at making fully transparent the financial management practices in each member state participant in the Joint Ministerial Council of British Overseas Territories at its fourth meeting in December 2015.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434234","Department of Health","false","2015-12-09","<br /><p>The number of inpatient deaths in child and adolescent mental health services is not collected centrally by the Department of Health.</p><br /><p>However, deaths of all patients detained under the Mental Health Act 1983 are notified to the Care Quality Commission (CQC). There were no such deaths reported in 2010/11. They reported that in 2011/12 one person aged 19 or under had died of unnatural causes and none had died of natural causes. In 2012/13 the CQC reported no deaths from unnatural causes and one from natural causes in detained patients aged 19 or under. Their report for 2013/14 (the most recent in the public domain) did not provide a breakdown by age of the deaths of detained patients.<a href="https://healthsharedservice.sharepoint.com/parliamentaryquestions/new_parliamentaryquestion_20151119_110130_94/PQ18769_89C393B4-BC9C-E511-8101-3863BB34EA08/PQ18769%20and%2018770.docx#_ftn1" target="_blank">[1]</a></p><br /><p>The Department for Education collect and publish data on the number of child deaths reviewed each year, including those where the death occurred in a mental health inpatient unit. These can be found in table 6 of the Statistical First Release ‘Child Death Reviews – year ending 31 March 2015’, available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-death-reviews-year-ending-31-march-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-death-reviews-year-ending-31-march-2015</a></p><br /><p>However, it is possible that the year in which the review took place, was later than the year in which the death occurred.</p><br /><p>The number of reviews of deaths occurring in a mental health inpatient unit have been suppressed in this table (shown with a ‘x’), indicating that there were 5 or fewer, and the actual figure is not shown in order to protect confidentiality. The number of reviews of deaths occurring in a mental health unit from 2010 to 2014 was nil.</p><br /> <br /> <br /><p><a href="https://healthsharedservice.sharepoint.com/parliamentaryquestions/new_parliamentaryquestion_20151119_110130_94/PQ18769_89C393B4-BC9C-E511-8101-3863BB34EA08/PQ18769%20and%2018770.docx#_ftnref1" target="_blank">[1]</a> Care Quality Commission: Monitoring the Mental Health Act” (annual publications for 2012/13 and 2013/14)</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-12-09T15:51:42.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434234/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434234/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-04","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what system is in place to record and publish statistics on child and adolescent deaths in psychiatric in-patient units.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","18769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434235","Department of Health","false","2015-12-09","<p>The number of inpatient deaths in child and adolescent mental health services is not collected centrally by the Department of Health.</p><br /><p>However, deaths of all patients detained under the Mental Health Act 1983 are notified to the Care Quality Commission (CQC). There were no such deaths reported in 2010/11. They reported that in 2011/12 one person aged 19 or under had died of unnatural causes and none had died of natural causes. In 2012/13 the CQC reported no deaths from unnatural causes and one from natural causes in detained patients aged 19 or under. Their report for 2013/14 (the most recent in the public domain) did not provide a breakdown by age of the deaths of detained patients.<a href="https://healthsharedservice.sharepoint.com/parliamentaryquestions/new_parliamentaryquestion_20151119_110130_94/PQ18769_89C393B4-BC9C-E511-8101-3863BB34EA08/PQ18769%20and%2018770.docx#_ftn1" target="_blank">[1]</a></p><br /><p>The Department for Education collect and publish data on the number of child deaths reviewed each year, including those where the death occurred in a mental health inpatient unit. These can be found in table 6 of the Statistical First Release ‘Child Death Reviews – year ending 31 March 2015’, available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-death-reviews-year-ending-31-march-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-death-reviews-year-ending-31-march-2015</a></p><br /><p>However, it is possible that the year in which the review took place, was later than the year in which the death occurred.</p><br /><p>The number of reviews of deaths occurring in a mental health inpatient unit have been suppressed in this table (shown with a ‘x’), indicating that there were 5 or fewer, and the actual figure is not shown in order to protect confidentiality. The number of reviews of deaths occurring in a mental health unit from 2010 to 2014 was nil.</p><br /> <br /> <br /><p><a href="https://healthsharedservice.sharepoint.com/parliamentaryquestions/new_parliamentaryquestion_20151119_110130_94/PQ18769_89C393B4-BC9C-E511-8101-3863BB34EA08/PQ18769%20and%2018770.docx#_ftnref1" target="_blank">[1]</a> Care Quality Commission: Monitoring the Mental Health Act” (annual publications for 2012/13 and 2013/14)</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-12-09T15:54:14.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434235/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434235/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-04","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many in-patients in child and adolescent psychiatric in-patient units have died in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","18770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434236","Department of Health","false","2015-12-09","<p>From 1 January 2016 mental health providers will be required to record all incidents of restraint involving children and young people in their returns to the Health and Social Care Information Centre. As with other health and care services, the Care Quality Commission is responsible for monitoring practice in inpatient children and adolescent psychiatric services.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-12-09T16:15:48.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434236/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/434236/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-04","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what systems and controls are in place for the recording, monitoring and oversight of the use of force and restraint on children and adolescents receiving psychiatric in-patient care.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","18771"
